## Part A — Extend plugin protocol for auth

### `pkg/pluginsdk`

- Add `SupportsAuth bool` to `GetterMetadata` and `SetterMetadata`.
- Add `AuthHandler` interface:
  ```go
  type AuthHandler interface {
      Authenticate(params map[string]any, out io.Writer) (map[string]string, error)
  }
  ```
- Add protocol types:
  ```go
  type authenticateRequest  struct { Params map[string]any    `json:"params"` }
  type authenticateResponse struct {
      Tokens map[string]string `json:"tokens,omitempty"`
      Error  string            `json:"error,omitempty"`
  }
  ```
- Add `--authenticate` case to `ServeGetter` and `ServeSetter`:
  decode `authenticateRequest` from stdin; cast handler to `AuthHandler`
  (return error response if not implemented); encode `authenticateResponse`.
- `--metadata` sets `supports_auth: true` when handler implements `AuthHandler`.

### `internal/plugin/protocol.go`

- Add mirror `authenticateRequest` / `authenticateResponse` types.

### `internal/plugin/external_getter.go` + `external_setter.go`

- Add `supportsAuth bool` from metadata.
- When true, implement `pluginspec.Authenticator.Authenticate(ctx, store)`:
  - Invoke binary `--authenticate` with empty params (consumer credentials
    are prompted inside the binary).
  - Pipe binary stderr → terminal so the user sees the auth URL.
  - Decode `authenticateResponse`; return any error.
  - Call `store.Set(g.name, key, value)` for each returned token.

### Tests (Part A) — extend existing test files

- `pkg/pluginsdk/pluginsdk_test.go`:
  - `--authenticate` with `AuthHandler` impl → tokens in response
  - `--authenticate` without `AuthHandler` → error response
  - `--metadata` with `AuthHandler` → `supports_auth: true`
- `internal/plugin/external_getter_test.go`:
  - `Authenticate` invokes binary, stores returned tokens
  - `Authenticate` propagates binary error
  - Getter without `supports_auth` does not implement `Authenticator`

