### `types.go`

TripIt v1 JSON shapes. Key detail: `Trip`, `AirObject.Segment`, `NoteObject`
may be a single object OR an array — use a generic `oneOrMany[T]` unmarshaler.

```go
type listTripResponse struct {
    Trip       oneOrMany[trip]       `json:"Trip"`
    AirObject  oneOrMany[airObject]  `json:"AirObject"`
    NoteObject oneOrMany[note]       `json:"NoteObject"`
}
type trip struct {
    ID              string `json:"id"`
    DisplayName     string `json:"display_name"`
    PrimaryLocation string `json:"primary_location"`
    StartDate       string `json:"start_date"`   // YYYY-MM-DD
    EndDate         string `json:"end_date"`
    RelativeURL     string `json:"relative_url"`
}
type airObject struct {
    TripID  string             `json:"trip_id"`
    Segment oneOrMany[segment] `json:"Segment"`
}
type segment struct {
    MarketingAirlineCode  string   `json:"marketing_airline_code"`
    MarketingFlightNumber string   `json:"marketing_flight_number"`
    StartAirportCode      string   `json:"start_airport_code"`
    EndAirportCode        string   `json:"end_airport_code"`
    StartDateTime         dateTime `json:"StartDateTime"`
    EndDateTime           dateTime `json:"EndDateTime"`
}
type dateTime struct {
    Date      string `json:"date"`
    Time      string `json:"time"`
    UTCOffset string `json:"utc_offset"` // e.g. "-06:00"
}
type note struct {
    TripID      string `json:"trip_id"`
    DisplayName string `json:"display_name"`
}
```

### `trips.go` (pure functions, testable without I/O)

Internal resolved type:
```go
type flight struct {
    FlightNumber string
    Origin       string
    Destination  string
    DepartTime   time.Time
    ArriveTime   time.Time
    Offset       string
}
```

Functions:
```
normaliseFlightTimeToTZ(dt dateTime) (time.Time, error)
resolveFlights(airObjects []airObject, tripID string) ([]flight, error)
resolveStartTime(t trip, flights []flight, ingressSec int) time.Time
resolveEndTime(t trip, flights []flight) time.Time
resolveLocation(t trip) string          // "Anywhere, Earth" if missing
tripEnded(endsAt time.Time, notes []note, tripID string, now time.Time) bool
ingressSeconds() int    // reads TRIPIT_INGRESS_TIME_MINUTES env var, default 0
```

### `client.go`

```go
type Client struct { httpClient *http.Client }
func NewClient(consumerKey, consumerSecret, accessToken, tokenSecret string) *Client
func (c *Client) ListTrips(ctx context.Context) (*listTripResponse, error)
func (c *Client) GetRequestToken(ctx context.Context, consumerKey, consumerSecret, callbackURL string) (token, secret string, _ error)
func (c *Client) GetAccessToken(ctx context.Context, consumerKey, consumerSecret, reqToken, reqSecret, verifier string) (token, secret string, _ error)
```

OAuth 1.0 HMAC-SHA1 signing via `github.com/dghubble/oauth1`.

### `browser.go` (used only during `--authenticate`)

Thin `chromedp` wrapper mirroring the Python `TripitWebDriver`:

```go
type Browser struct { ctx context.Context; cancel context.CancelFunc }
func NewBrowser(ctx context.Context) (*Browser, error)  // headless Chrome via chromedp
func (b *Browser) SetGDPRCookies() error
func (b *Browser) Visit(url string) error
func (b *Browser) FillIn(selector, value string) error
func (b *Browser) ClickButton(text string) error
func (b *Browser) PageSource() (string, error)
func (b *Browser) Close()
```

`KEEP_BROWSER_OPEN=true` suppresses `Close()` (matches Python's
`KEEP_BROWSER_WINDOWS_OPEN`).

### `handler.go`

**`Metadata()`** → name `"tripit"`, `MinInterval: "5m"`, `SupportsAuth: true`,
and `ParamSpecs` for `consumer_key`, `consumer_secret`, `access_token`,
`token_secret`, `ingress_minutes`.

**`GetEvents(params)`**:
1. Extract params; resolve ingress via `ingressSeconds()` (param overrides env var).
2. Build `Client`; call `ListTrips`.
3. For each trip: `resolveFlights`, `resolveStartTime`, `resolveEndTime`,
   `resolveLocation`, `tripEnded`.
4. Filter to `startsAt <= now <= endsAt`.
5. Return `[]pluginsdk.Event`.

**`Authenticate(params, out)`**:
1. Pick random local port; register callback handler on `localhost:PORT`.
2. Call `client.GetRequestToken(…, "http://localhost:PORT/callback")`.
3. Print to `out`:
   ```
   Open this URL to authorise status with TripIt:

     https://www.tripit.com/oauth/authorize?oauth_token=TOKEN&oauth_callback=http://localhost:PORT/callback

   Waiting for authorisation...
   ```
4. Block until callback arrives (with context timeout).
5. Call `client.GetAccessToken` with verifier.
6. Return `{"access_token": "…", "token_secret": "…"}`.

### `main.go`

```go
func main() {
    os.Exit(pluginsdk.ServeGetter(handler.New(), os.Args[1:], os.Stdin, os.Stdout))
}
```

